The paper deals with constructing good distance lattices, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and discrete structures (cs.DS). The use of high dimensional expanders and Ramanujan complexes suggests that the paper may also fall under computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the proof techniques used involve coboundary expansion and spherical buildings, which are concepts in algebraic topology (cs.SD).
